These statistics are not static in time and follow a specific population of infection through case resolution.
Some academics have tried to calculate these numbers for specific populations.
The Centre for Evidence-Based Medicine at the University of Oxford estimates that the case-fatality rate from infection to pandemic, overall, is between 0.1% and 0.39%.
The higher estimate of this range is compatible with the results of the first random test for COVID-19 in Germany and with a statistical study that analyzed the impact of the tests on CFR estimates.
The WHO says the pandemic can be controlled.
